<section class="section" style="padding-top:0">
  <h2 class="h2">What the kit teaches</h2>
  <div class="feature-grid">
    <div class="pill"><strong>DNA ↔ RNA</strong><span> Complementary base pairing and polarity</span></div>
    <div class="pill"><strong>Transcription</strong><span> Template strand and 5′ to 3′ building</span></div>
    <div class="pill"><strong>Translation</strong><span> Codons, amino acids, and short peptides</span></div>
    <div class="pill"><strong>Mutations</strong><span> Point changes and frameshifts with effects</span></div>
    <div class="pill"><strong>Epigenetics</strong><span> Methylation and regulatory RNA (advanced)</span></div>
    <div class="pill"><strong>Classroom ready</strong><span> Activities in 15 to 45 minutes</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .feature-grid {
    display:grid;
    gap:.55rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(1, minmax(0,1fr));
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .feature-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr)); }
  }
  .pill {
    display:flex; gap:.5rem; align-items:center; padding:.6rem .8rem;
    border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:9999px;
    background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.02);
  }
  .pill strong { font-weight:800; }
  .pill span { color: var(--muted); }
</style>

